      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">1. Initialize HET on a normal page</h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>HET enhances existing HTML. Start by loading the script and calling <code>init()</code>.</p>
        <p>Without JavaScript, the link still performs a full page load. With HET running, <code>het-target</code> opts the link into progressive enhancement.</p>
        <p>Relevant reference:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="reference/requests#core-attributes">Core attributes</a></li>
          <li><a href="reference/api#initconfig"><code>init(config)</code></a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <form method="post" action="/preview" target="tutorial-preview" data-tutorial-form>
        <input type="hidden" name="html" data-editor-output="html">
        <input type="hidden" name="js" data-editor-output="js">
        <input type="hidden" name="css" data-editor-output="css">

        <div class="mb-3">
          <label class="form-label fw-semibold" for="html-source">HTML</label>
          <textarea id="html-source" class="d-none" data-editor="html">&lt;main het-pane="main">
  &lt;h1>Dashboard&lt;/h1>
  &lt;a href="/reports" het-target="main">Reports&lt;/a>
&lt;/main></textarea>
          <div class="editor-host" data-editor-host="html"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-3">
          <label class="form-label fw-semibold" for="js-source">JavaScript</label>
          <textarea id="js-source" class="d-none" data-editor="js">HET.init();</textarea>
          <div class="editor-host" data-editor-host="js"></div>
        </div>
        <textarea class="d-none" data-editor="css"></textarea>

        <button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit">Submit</button>
      </form>

